question - https://www.codewars.com/kata/57d2807295497e652b000139/train/python

solution 

def averages(arr):
    average = []
    
    if arr is None or len(arr) <= 1:
        average = []
    else:
        for i in range(len(arr) - 1):
            average.append((arr[i] + arr[i + 1])/2)
       
    return average
